title: Appointment to the Hospital Authority
content_text:
p>The Government announced today (October 13) the appointment of two new members 
and the reappointment of three members to the Hospital Authority (HA). The two new members are Dr Margaret Chung Wai-ling and Ms Polly Lau Mo-yee who 
will serve for two-year terms with effect from December 1. Dr Margaret Chung, an expert in Biomedicine, is currently a member of the Health 
and Medical Development Advisory Committee and the Rehabilitation Advisory 
Committee. She has been an advocate for patients' self-help and mutual help for

Committee. She has been an advocate for patients' self-help and mutual help for 
many years and is a founding committee member of the Alliance for Patients' 
Mutual Help Organisations as well as the Hong Kong Arthritis and Rheumatism 
Foundation.  Ms Polly Lau is a cluster manager (Physiotherapy) of the Kowloon Central Cluster 
of the HA. Her appointment follows the long-established practice of the 
Government to include a staff member of the HA on its board. Ms Lau will fill

Government to include a staff member of the HA on its board. Ms Lau will fill 
the vacancy left behind by Dr Loretta Yam, who resigned from the board in June. 
Ms Lau is currently the president of the Hong Kong Physiotherapy Association. Mr Paul Yu Shiu-tin and Dr Anthony Ho Yiu-wah have been reappointed as members 
of the HA. Professor Thomas Wong Kwok-shing has also been reappointed in his 
capacity as the Dean of the Faculty of Health and Social Science at the Hong

capacity as the Dean of the Faculty of Health and Social Science at the Hong 
Kong Polytechnic University. All the reappointments are also for a term of two 
years with effect from December 1. Meanwhile, five members will retire from the board on December 1. They are Mrs 
Eleanor Ling Lee Ching-man, Miss Eliza Chan Ching-har, Miss Iris Chan Sui-ching, 
Mr Lo Chung-hing and Dr Lily Chiang.  The Secretary for Health, Welfare and Food, Dr York Chow, expressed his

gratitude to the retiring members for their advice and contribution to the HA 
over the years. "My thanks go in particular to Mrs Eleanor Ling who has been the chairperson of 
HA's Human Resources Committee, Staff Appeals Committee and Board of Trustees of 
the Hospital Authority Provident Fund Scheme. My gratitude also goes to Miss 
Eliza Chan and Dr Lily Chiang who are chairpersons of the Public Complaints 
Committee and Supporting Services Development Committee respectively. Their 
advice is invaluable and has helped the HA develop and realise its mission," he
